title: Regular topological space
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A topological space $$X$$ is called //regular,// if for every closed nonempty $$A\subseteq X$$ and every point $$x\in X\setminus A$$ there exist disjoint neighborhoods of $$A$$ and $$x.$$